td.p:
The possibility of laying down national provisions with regard to the period of validity provided for in [Council] Directive 91/439/EEC [of 29 July 1991 on driving licences (
OJ 1991 L 237, p. 1
)] leads to the coexistence of different rules in different Member States and over 110 different models of driving licences valid in the Member States. This creates problems of transparency for citizens, police forces and the administrations responsible for the administration of driving licences and leads to the falsification of documents which sometimes date back several decades.
